## Inline results from tbl_regression() {#inline_text_tbl_regression}

Similar syntax is used to report results from
[`tbl_regression()`](http://www.danieldsjoberg.com/gtsummary/reference/tbl_regression.html)
and
[`tbl_uvregression()`](http://www.danieldsjoberg.com/gtsummary/reference/tbl_uvregression.html)
tables. Refer to the [`tbl_regression()`
vignette](http://www.danieldsjoberg.com/gtsummary/articles/tbl_regression.html)
if you need detailed guidance on using these functions.

Let's first create a regression model.


::: {.cell hash='gt-summary_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-4_889a35f87706b5d4a9bb5892727b165d'}

````{.cell-code}
```{{r}}
# build logistic regression model
m1 <- glm(response ~ age + stage, trial, family = binomial(link = "logit"))
```
````
:::


Now summarize the results with `tbl_regression()`; exponentiate to get
the odds ratios.


::: {.cell hash='gt-summary_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-5_511043311feda63e0519413966ab63c7'}

````{.cell-code}
```{{r}}
tbl_m1 <- tbl_regression(m1, exponentiate = TRUE)
tbl_m1
```
````

